data.name: Herb-Crusted Pork Tenderloin
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy pork tenderloin coated in a flavorful herb crust, perfect for a quick yet impressive dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix together the garlic powder, dried thyme, dried rosemary, salt, and black pepper.
Rub the pork tenderloin with olive oil and then coat it evenly with the herb mixture.
Place the tenderloin on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Roast in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes, or until the internal temperature reaches 145째F (63째C).
Remove from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
